250 g Ground Pork
6 unit(s) Flour Tortillas
170 g Coleslaw Cabbage Mix
113 g Mushrooms
1 tbsp Garlic Puree
9 g Moo Shu Spice Blend
1 tbsp Sesame Oil
4 tbsp Hoisin Sauce
1 tbsp Soy Sauce
7 g Cilantro
1 tbsp Seasoned Rice Vinegar
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Cut mushrooms into 1/4-inch slices.
Roughly chop cilantro.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high.
When hot, add half the sesame oil, then mushrooms.
Cook for 2-3 min, stirring occasionally, until mushrooms soften slightly.
Season with salt and pepper.

To the pan with mushrooms, add pork. Cook for 4-5 min, breaking up pork into smaller pieces, until no pink remains.**
Add Moo Shu Spice Blend and garlic puree. Cook for 1 min, stirring often, until fragrant. Season with salt and pepper.
Add hoisin, soy sauce and half the coleslaw mix.
Cook for 2-3 mins, stirring often, until cabbage wilts.
Take the pan off heat.

Wrap tortillas in paper towels.
Microwave for 1 min, until tortillas are warm and flexible. (TIP: You can skip this step if you don't want to warm the tortillas!)

In a medium bowl, whisk together rice vinegar, 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) sugar and remaining sesame oil. Season with salt and pepper.
Add remaining coleslaw mix and cilantro, then toss to combine.

Divide pork mixture and slaw between tortillas.
Divide tacos between plates.